general_rem: One of the "92 species [that] had successfully established exclusively from plant material at the restoration sites"  (bc-00-01-14, p.229). These "plant material species" form a group that "consists of typical flood meadow species that were part of the vegetation at the donor sites and present neither in the established vegetation, seed bank nor in the close surroundings of the restoration site" (bc-00-01-14, p.227). Most of these species (76 over 92) were also identified from germinated seedlings (bc-00-01-14, p.226) in the analysed plant material samples. A total of 124 species "that could be unequivocally attributed to the donor populations"  (bc-00-01-14, p.228) were identified from a germination experiment in these plant material samples. We take into account only the restoration sites at > 1 km from donor sites, i.e. the restor sites in NSG Michelried and nearby.
objectives: bc-00-01-14 : "… in the present project aiming at the re-establishment of species-rich flood meadows by the transfer of plant material on a large scale (50 ha) along the northern Upper Rhine".

"PD. Dr. Tobias W. Donath : tdonath@ecology.uni-kiel.de / Annette Otte, Prof. Dr. Dr. habil. Dr. h.c. (TSU) (Retired professor (former Director until 9/2018)

general_rem: One of the "92 species [that] had successfully established exclusively from plant material at the restoration sites"  (bc-00-01-14, p.229). These "plant material species" form a group that "consists of typical flood meadow species that were part of the vegetation at the donor sites and present neither in the established vegetation, seed bank nor in the close surroundings of the restoration site" (bc-00-01-14, p.227). Most of these species (76 over 92) were also identified from germinated seedlings (bc-00-01-14, p.226) in the analysed plant material samples. A total of 124 species "that could be unequivocally attributed to the donor populations"  (bc-00-01-14, p.228) were identified from a germination experiment in these plant material samples. We take into account only the restoration sites at > 1 km from donor sites, i.e. the restor sites in NSG Michelried and nearby.
objectives: bc-00-01-14 : "… in the present project aiming at the re-establishment of species-rich flood meadows by the transfer of plant material on a large scale (50 ha) along the northern Upper Rhine".
lieu_dit: Restor sites in NSG Michelried and nearby

"PD. Dr. Tobias W. Donath : tdonath@ecology.uni-kiel.de / Annette Otte, Prof. Dr. Dr. habil. Dr. h.c. (TSU) (Retired professor (former Director until 9/2018)
) : annette.otte@umwelt.uni-giessen.de."
general_rem: One of the "92 species [that] had successfully established exclusively from plant material at the restoration sites"  (bc-00-01-14, p.229). These "plant material species" form a group that "consists of typical flood meadow species that were part of the vegetation at the donor sites and present neither in the established vegetation, seed bank nor in the close surroundings of the restoration site" (bc-00-01-14, p.227). Most of these species (76 over 92) were also identified from germinated seedlings (bc-00-01-14, p.226) in the analysed plant material samples. A total of 124 species "that could be unequivocally attributed to the donor populations"  (bc-00-01-14, p.228) were identified from a germination experiment in these plant material samples. We take into account only the restoration sites at > 1 km from donor sites, i.e. the restor sites in NSG Michelried and nearby.
objectives: bc-00-01-14 : "… in the present project aiming at the re-establishment of species-rich flood meadows by the transfer of plant material on a large scale (50 ha) along the northern Upper Rhine".
lieu_dit: Restor sites in NSG Michelried and nearby

objectives: il-00-00-18 : "For the re-creation of species-rich grasslands, on former arable land, suitable habitat conditions must be restored in order to enhance the establishment and long-term survival of target species, which are typical for ancient low-productive grasslands, and to prevent the spreading of nontarget species such as common arable weeds or potentially dominant ruderals" ; + to study "The effects of different restoration measures and management variants on the vegetation development of newly created calcareous grasslands".

general_rem: One of the "92 species [that] had successfully established exclusively from plant material at the restoration sites"  (bc-00-01-14, p.229). These "plant material species" form a group that "consists of typical flood meadow species that were part of the vegetation at the donor sites and present neither in the established vegetation, seed bank nor in the close surroundings of the restoration site" (bc-00-01-14, p.227). Most of these species (76 over 92) were also identified from germinated seedlings (bc-00-01-14, p.226) in the analysed plant material samples. A total of 124 species "that could be unequivocally attributed to the donor populations"  (bc-00-01-14, p.228) were identified from a germination experiment in these plant material samples. We take into account only the restoration sites at > 1 km from donor sites, i.e. the restor sites in NSG Michelried and nearby.

general_rem: bc-00-01-00 : "A ma connaissance il y a eu une seule autre manipe de renforcement, que nous avons mené avec l'AGENC en janvier 2000.  Il ne s'agissait d'ailleurs pas en soi d'une manipe de renforcement, mais plutôt d'un essai "technique". En effet, la population concernée (col de Teghime) est la seule que nous étudions qui se porte très bien (proba d'extinction à 50 ans = 0). L'idée était de tester le renforcement d'une population à partir de graines de la collection du CBNP, et de suivre la germination et la survie des plantules."

general_rem: One of the "92 species [that] had successfully established exclusively from plant material at the restoration sites"  (bc-00-01-14, p.229). These "plant material species" form a group that "consists of typical flood meadow species that were part of the vegetation at the donor sites and present neither in the established vegetation, seed bank nor in the close surroundings of the restoration site" (bc-00-01-14, p.227). Most of these species (76 over 92) were also identified from germinated seedlings (bc-00-01-14, p.226) in the analysed plant material samples. A total of 124 species "that could be unequivocally attributed to the donor populations"  (bc-00-01-14, p.228) were identified from a germination experiment in these plant material samples. We take into account only the restoration sites at > 1 km from donor sites, i.e. the restor sites in NSG Michelried and nearby.
objectives: bc-00-01-14 : "… in the present project aiming at the re-establishment of species-rich flood meadows by the transfer of plant material on a large scale (50 ha) along the northern Upper Rhine".

general_rem: One of the "92 species [that] had successfully established exclusively from plant material at the restoration sites"  (bc-00-01-14, p.229). These "plant material species" form a group that "consists of typical flood meadow species that were part of the vegetation at the donor sites and present neither in the established vegetation, seed bank nor in the close surroundings of the restoration site" (bc-00-01-14, p.227). Most of these species (76 over 92) were also identified from germinated seedlings (bc-00-01-14, p.226) in the analysed plant material samples. A total of 124 species "that could be unequivocally attributed to the donor populations"  (bc-00-01-14, p.228) were identified from a germination experiment in these plant material samples. We take into account only the restoration sites at > 1 km from donor sites, i.e. the restor sites in NSG Michelried and nearby.

general_rem: Dans il-00-00-18 : Uniquement les espèces étant à la fois "target species" (t in Table 5) and "species proven to be transferred by hay onto restoration fields with hay" (origin h dans Table 5). Prise en compte uniquement de la restoration sur le site éloigné (RF2526) de 800m par rapport à la réserve où est prélevé le matériel d'origine, l'autre site étant adjacent à la réserve donc est plutôt considéré comme de la gestion de site.
objectives: il-00-00-18 : "For the re-creation of species-rich grasslands, on former arable land, suitable habitat conditions must be restored in order to enhance the establishment and long-term survival of target species, which are typical for ancient low-productive grasslands, and to prevent the spreading of nontarget species such as common arable weeds or potentially dominant ruderals" ; + to study "The effects of different restoration measures and management variants on the vegetation development of newly created calcareous grasslands".

isol_caus: du fait de la faible distance (800 m) et que ce sont des espèces de prairie susceptibles d'être dispersées assez facilement par le vent, les animaux, l'homme.
pop_hab: Our study has been carried out on four different restoration fields (RF) with areas of 1.3–3.2 ha that had been used for cultivation of barley and rye until 1992. [...]. RF 2526 was isolated between intensively cultivated arable fields in an open treeless landscape.
biol_rem: "Between end of July and beginning of September 1993, diaspore-containing fresh hay was cut in the nature reserve ca. 4 cm above soil surface"
meth_rem: il-00-00-18 : sheep grazing in late spring and late summer
monit_rem: il-00-00-18 : "percentage cover of all phanerogam species"
res_rem: il-00-00-18 : "the transfer of autochthonous hay was a very efficient method to overcome dispersal limitation and to allow a quick establishment of target species" ; "hay transfer allowed not only quick establishment of target species during the initial restoration phase, but also their persistence over 9 years"

objectives: "Ainsi, l’objectif de ce travail est de créer une nouvelle population viable sur le long terme en s’appuyant sur un dispositif expérimental permettant de mieux comprendre l’écologie de l’espèce, et d’optimiser les mécanismes de restauration."
context_rem: "Dans le cadre de la mesure compensatoire liée aux travaux d’élargissement de la RD61 entre Lunel et la Grande-Motte, la destruction et le risque d’impact sur des pieds de Nivéole d’été (Leucojum aestivum) nécessite le déplacement des individus concernés (sous forme de bulbes) afin de recréer une nouvelle population viable. "
altern_en: Pop creation within extent of occurrence
increase_meth: Plantation de bulbes, récolte des graines qui en sont issues, semis en serre, récolte des bulbes...
meth_rem:
"Un programme de restauration écologique est en cours pour re-profiler les berges de la roubine principale du site selon des pentes plus douces."
"La plantation des bulbes aura lieu entre août et octobre 2018, afin de déplacer les individus durant leur période végétative et avant les premières pluies. Si nécessaire, le site aura été au préalable débroussaillé, avec l’extraction manuelle de la matière végétale en-dehors de celui-ci. "
"Les bulbes seront plantés sur le site de compensation dans des trous réalisés avec une bêche coupante ou une tarière. Les parties vivantes de la végétation (notamment les systèmes racinaires) seront extrait pour limiter la concurrence la première année. La « profondeur moyenne idéale » sera définie en fonction de celle observée lors du prélèvement des bulbes."

biol_rem: Les pieds n'étaient plus présents au moment de la collecte.
meth_rem: Déplacement par banquettes de sol avec une mini-pelle mécanique. Préparation du site de réception par décaissement et aplanissement.
det_csq: Forte perturbation du milieu. Mauvaise gestion par l'agriculteur. Création d'une APPB.
mortality: Mauvais état du matériel initial. Mauvaise gestion du site.

context_rem: Causes de déclin : Plus de gélifraction entraînant une granulométrie non conforme. Stabilisation des éboulis par les graminées.
altern_en: Pop creation within extent of occurrence

objectives:
Cicatrisation des milieux littoraux.
Réduction de l'érosion.
The project's purpose was to re-establish a viable black vulture population in the Causses, which would be no longer dependent on food handouts
context_rem: Les vautours ont beaucoup souffert de persécution directe par les humains jusqu'au 20ème siècle.
sit_rem: les sites vitaux pour la population de Vautour moine sont situés dans l’espace d’adhésion du Parc, non dans le Cœur du Parc, et ne bénéficient donc pas de la réglementation relative aux Parcs nationaux concernant les mesures de restauration ou de préservation des écosystèmes
biol_rem: Les oiseaux lâchés provenaient de deux types de structures : les centres espagnols de récupération de la faune sauvage (8 centres ont fourni 30 oiseaux) ; les centres de reproduction en captivité et parcs zoologiques (12 centres de divers pays européens ont fourni 23 oiseaux).
time_exsitu: At least a year for the aviary method
meth_rem: Mis en place de placettes d'alimentation directement gérées par les éleveurs (54 placettes en 2010). Organisation de tournées d'équarrissage.
monit_rem: The birds were tagged with an engraved metal band attached to one tarsus and with a plastic band to the other for long distance identification. In addition, aviary-released immature were equipped with a radio transmitter, with a lifespan of 1 year.
det_csq:
An agreement has been signed between the beneficiary and EDF (the French Electricity Company) for the neutralisation of the most dangerous power lines.
From a touristic point of view, the return of the vultures in the region is also very positive
res_rem:
First wild chick born in 1996.
Depuis 1996, date de la première reproduction en liberté, 59 Vautours moines ont été produits dans la nature.
mortality:
The electric power lines are responsible for 75% of the mortality cases by collision or electrocution of the birds of preys in the Causses.
Les chutes de nids étaient très fréquentes lors des premières tentatives de reproduction, dues très probablement à l’inexpérience des jeunes oiseaux nicheurs.
Empoisonnements.

objectives:
Programme LIFE-Nature : Sauvetage de Viola hispida et Biscutella neustriaca en Val de Seine.
Sauvegarde d'une endémique en vallée de la Seine.
context_rem: Causes de déclin : Renfermement du milieu par les graminées suite à un changement progressif des pratiques culturales. Auto-incompatibilité de la plante -> un grand nombre d'individus par populations est nécessaire. Le pâturage extensif (peu à peu abandonné) aide à la dispersion des graines.
pop_hab:
Pelouse calcicole mésophile à Seslérie
bleuâtre

potentials:
"PD. Dr. Tobias W. Donath : tdonath@ecology.uni-kiel.de / Annette Otte, Prof. Dr. Dr. habil. Dr. h.c. (TSU) (Retired professor (former Director until 9/2018)
) : annette.otte@umwelt.uni-giessen.de."
general_rem: One of the "92 species [that] had successfully established exclusively from plant material at the restoration sites"  (bc-00-01-14, p.229). These "plant material species" form a group that "consists of typical flood meadow species that were part of the vegetation at the donor sites and present neither in the established vegetation, seed bank nor in the close surroundings of the restoration site" (bc-00-01-14, p.227). Most of these species (76 over 92) were also identified from germinated seedlings (bc-00-01-14, p.226) in the analysed plant material samples. A total of 124 species "that could be unequivocally attributed to the donor populations"  (bc-00-01-14, p.228) were identified from a germination experiment in these plant material samples. We take into account only the restoration sites at > 1 km from donor sites, i.e. the restor sites in NSG Michelried and nearby.
objectives: bc-00-01-14 : "… in the present project aiming at the re-establishment of species-rich flood meadows by the transfer of plant material on a large scale (50 ha) along the northern Upper Rhine".
lieu_dit: Restor sites in NSG Michelried and nearby

general_rem: One of the "92 species [that] had successfully established exclusively from plant material at the restoration sites"  (bc-00-01-14, p.229). These "plant material species" form a group that "consists of typical flood meadow species that were part of the vegetation at the donor sites and present neither in the established vegetation, seed bank nor in the close surroundings of the restoration site" (bc-00-01-14, p.227). Most of these species (76 over 92) were also identified from germinated seedlings (bc-00-01-14, p.226) in the analysed plant material samples. A total of 124 species "that could be unequivocally attributed to the donor populations"  (bc-00-01-14, p.228) were identified from a germination experiment in these plant material samples. We take into account only the restoration sites at > 1 km from donor sites, i.e. the restor sites in NSG Michelried and nearby.
objectives: bc-00-01-14 : "… in the present project aiming at the re-establishment of species-rich flood meadows by the transfer of plant material on a large scale (50 ha) along the northern Upper Rhine".
lieu_dit: Restor sites in NSG Michelried and nearby

general_rem: Dans il-00-00-18 : Uniquement les espèces étant à la fois "target species" (t in Table 5) and "species proven to be transferred by hay onto restoration fields with hay" (origin h dans Table 5). Prise en compte uniquement de la restoration sur le site éloigné (RF2526) de 800m par rapport à la réserve où est prélevé le matériel d'origine, l'autre site étant adjacent à la réserve donc est plutôt considéré comme de la gestion de site.
objectives: il-00-00-18 : "For the re-creation of species-rich grasslands, on former arable land, suitable habitat conditions must be restored in order to enhance the establishment and long-term survival of target species, which are typical for ancient low-productive grasslands, and to prevent the spreading of nontarget species such as common arable weeds or potentially dominant ruderals" ; + to study "The effects of different restoration measures and management variants on the vegetation development of newly created calcareous grasslands".
altern_en: Pop creation within extent of occurrence
isol_caus: du fait de la faible distance (800 m) et que ce sont des espèces de prairie susceptibles d'être dispersées assez facilement par le vent, les animaux, l'homme.
pop_hab: Our study has been carried out on four different restoration fields (RF) with areas of 1.3–3.2 ha that had been used for cultivation of barley and rye until 1992. [...]. RF 2526 was isolated between intensively cultivated arable fields in an open treeless landscape.
biol_rem: "Between end of July and beginning of September 1993, diaspore-containing fresh hay was cut in the nature reserve ca. 4 cm above soil surface"
meth_rem: il-00-00-18 : sheep grazing in late spring and late summer
monit_rem: il-00-00-18 : "percentage cover of all phanerogam species"
res_rem: il-00-00-18 : "the transfer of autochthonous hay was a very efficient method to overcome dispersal limitation and to allow a quick establishment of target species" ; "hay transfer allowed not only quick establishment of target species during the initial restoration phase, but also their persistence over 9 years"
